---
pagination:
  data: news
  size: 1
  alias: post
permalink: "{{ post.oldUrl }}"
eleventyExcludeFromCollections: true
---
{#
  301-style redirect from the retired /news/<slug>/ URL to the post's new
  typed home (/stories/, /archive/, or /learn/). GitHub Pages is a static
  host with no server-side 301, so we use a meta-refresh + a canonical link
  (the SEO-equivalent on a static site) and a visible fallback link. One page
  is generated per moved post, so EVERY legacy URL resolves.
#}<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="utf-8">
  <meta http-equiv="refresh" content="0; url={{ post.url }}">
  <link rel="canonical" href="{{ site.origin }}{{ post.url }}">
  <meta name="robots" content="noindex, follow">
  <title>Moved: {{ post.title }}</title>
  <script>location.replace({{ post.url | dump | safe }});</script>
</head>
<body>
  <p>This page has moved. If you are not redirected automatically,
     <a href="{{ post.url }}">continue to "{{ post.title }}"</a>.</p>
</body>
</html>
